1
00:00:35,490 --> 00:00:39,660
You have a choice
with the time you have left.

2
00:00:40,830 --> 00:00:44,750
If you give up being a doctor,
you'll have more time.

3
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:46,980
If you choose to stay a doctor...

4
00:00:46,980 --> 00:00:49,660
you'll risk all the time
you have left.

5
00:00:49,660 --> 00:00:53,580
Does living as a doctor mean
everything to you?

6
00:01:10,910 --> 00:01:12,280
Pull ourselves together!

7
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:16,510
Please move aside!

8
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:23,800
- Please move aside!
- Excuse us!

9
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,100
How is the patient?

10
00:01:25,130 --> 00:01:26,640
She's not breathing.

11
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:28,690
Saturation level is 78.

12
00:01:28,690 --> 00:01:31,060
Intubation will be difficult
due to nasal bleeding.

13
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:35,700
You don't know what pain is.

14
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:39,420
What is it you feel for the
patients who do know?

15
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:42,630
Sympathy?

16
00:01:44,030 --> 00:01:45,510
Is it curiosity?

17
00:01:48,610 --> 00:01:50,950
Ri Hye. Ri Hye, it's me.

18
00:01:50,950 --> 00:01:52,820
I'm sorry, but you can't go in.

19
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,910
You'll see your son now.

20
00:02:22,870 --> 00:02:25,270
Did we do the right thing?

21
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:29,070
She wanted to die enough
to jump off the building.

22
00:02:29,070 --> 00:02:31,230
Is it okay...

23
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:35,050
to keep her alive like this?

24
00:02:35,050 --> 00:02:36,450
We're not her friends.

25
00:02:36,450 --> 00:02:38,910
We can't decipher life
or death for her.

26
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,610
We're doctors.

27
00:02:41,610 --> 00:02:44,290
What also worries me here is that...

28
00:02:44,290 --> 00:02:47,670
if she wrote an advance
directive or a DNR order,

29
00:02:47,670 --> 00:02:50,180
wouldn't the intubation
be of an issue?

30
00:02:50,180 --> 00:02:51,250
Then what?

31
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:53,030
That we shouldn't have
done anything?

32
00:02:53,030 --> 00:02:54,700
No, that's not it, but...

33
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:56,780
Geez, what is the "right" thing here?

34
00:02:56,780 --> 00:02:58,850
Let's report this to Dr. Cha first.

35
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:24,740
Ms. Yu Ri Hye?

36
00:03:24,740 --> 00:03:26,740
How is her condition?

37
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,630
Take her to the ICU.

38
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:33,650
Okay, I'll be right there.

39
00:03:53,050 --> 00:03:55,780
[ Doctor John ]
[ Episode 11: Consolation ]

40
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:07,430
I heard the patient has a child.

41
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:10,650
No mother would think of dying
when she has a child.

42
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:14,920
This means something caused
her to want to jump.

43
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:17,120
My gut tells me...

44
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:20,520
that her jumping off won't
be the end of this incident.

45
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,430
We have a problem.

46
00:04:36,430 --> 00:04:38,770
Ms. Yu Ri Hye.

47
00:04:38,770 --> 00:04:40,330
What? What is it?

48
00:04:40,330 --> 00:04:41,390
Someone...

49
00:04:41,390 --> 00:04:43,480
shut off Yu Ri Hye's ventilator.

50
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,150
What?

51
00:04:45,150 --> 00:04:46,300
Who?

52
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,060
I said, who is it?

53
00:04:50,060 --> 00:04:51,970
Well, the thing is...

54
00:04:51,970 --> 00:04:55,260
When they discovered
the ventilator was off

55
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:57,120
in the ICU...

56
00:04:58,130 --> 00:04:59,790
right next to the patient...

57
00:04:59,790 --> 00:05:01,090
Who are you?

58
00:05:17,890 --> 00:05:19,850
- Dr. Cha?
- Yes.

59
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,230
I'm sorry!

60
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:26,850
What are you talking about?

61
00:05:26,850 --> 00:05:29,180
The entire ICU is in chaos, Director.

62
00:05:29,180 --> 00:05:31,410
Someone reported it,
so the police are on their way.

63
00:05:31,410 --> 00:05:33,200
How can something
like this happen?

64
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:36,610
And?

65
00:05:36,610 --> 00:05:37,980
Who did this?

66
00:05:37,980 --> 00:05:40,050
Who else could it be? Huh?

67
00:05:40,050 --> 00:05:42,400
- Who else would it be?
- Dr. Kwon.

68
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:43,960
Please don't jump to conclusions.

69
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:46,360
Find the culprit through an
investigation, not speculations.

70
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:48,980
Yes! The police are on their way.

71
00:05:48,980 --> 00:05:51,340
The police are headed to
our hospital. The police!

72
00:05:51,340 --> 00:05:53,230
Director, please stay calm.

73
00:05:53,230 --> 00:05:54,690
How can I stay calm?

74
00:05:54,690 --> 00:05:56,740
Someone turned off
a patient's ventilator!

75
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:00,590
This is clearly an attempted murder.

76
00:06:00,590 --> 00:06:03,520
Fortunately, she was
still able to breathe.

77
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:05,990
This could've been
a murder case. A murder!

78
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:08,540
Dr. Cha is in charge of this patient.

79
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:10,810
Kang Shi Young is her
doctor-in-charge.

80
00:06:10,810 --> 00:06:12,200
You all know this, right?

81
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,880
Tell everyone to cooperate
with the investigation.

82
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:17,650
I'll be observing...

83
00:06:17,650 --> 00:06:20,120
how this turns out.

84
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:25,140
I knew this day would come.

85
00:06:26,710 --> 00:06:29,490
Gosh, this is insane.

86
00:06:29,490 --> 00:06:31,800
Should we summon
Shi Young and Mi Rae?

87
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,330
And ask if they know anything?

88
00:06:33,330 --> 00:06:35,150
If they know something...

89
00:06:35,150 --> 00:06:37,360
then it'd be a problem,
don't you know?

90
00:06:38,460 --> 00:06:40,320
Send Dr. Cha to the Legal Team.

91
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,680
Before the police arrive. Hurry.

92
00:07:11,690 --> 00:07:13,680
No, you can't go in.

93
00:07:20,460 --> 00:07:21,740
Shi Young...

94
00:07:21,740 --> 00:07:22,860
Auntie.

95
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,550
Dr. Cha is over at the
legal department.

96
00:07:31,550 --> 00:07:32,910
The legal department?

97
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:35,830
Chief sent him to
Attorney Han Myung Oh.

98
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:39,480
You guys don't know anything, right?

99
00:07:41,390 --> 00:07:42,770
What about Yu Ri Hye?

100
00:07:42,770 --> 00:07:45,050
We moved her to a
general ward for now.

101
00:07:45,050 --> 00:07:46,630
Thank you, Auntie.

102
00:07:51,810 --> 00:07:53,120
[ MICU ]

103
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,580
[ Restricted Area ]

104
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:03,490
[ Department of
Pain Medicine: Yu Ri Hye ]

105
00:08:07,660 --> 00:08:10,010
- Is this the ventilator?
- Yes.

106
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:16,750
I'm Chief Min Tae Kyung of
Anesthesiology and Pain Medicine.

107
00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:18,120
Nice to meet you.

108
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:20,760
I'm Officer Kim Jung Rok
from the Gangnam Station.

109
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:25,770
We moved Yu Ri Hye to
a general ward for now.

110
00:08:25,770 --> 00:08:27,000
How is her condition?

111
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,600
She is breathing on her own.
And still unconscious.

112
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:33,060
Please tell us what
happened in detail.

113
00:08:33,060 --> 00:08:34,460
Well...

114
00:08:34,460 --> 00:08:38,010
it was around the end of
visiting hours in the ICU.

115
00:08:38,010 --> 00:08:40,190
And what are your visiting hours?

116
00:08:40,190 --> 00:08:43,110
At our hospital, it's
from 4:30 p.m. to 5 p.m.

117
00:08:43,110 --> 00:08:46,070
However, Yu Ri Hye
didn't have any visitors.

118
00:08:46,070 --> 00:08:48,810
But that's the time
outsiders are in and out.

119
00:08:48,810 --> 00:08:51,240
Please go ahead. In detail.

120
00:08:53,090 --> 00:08:54,500
Who are you here to see?

121
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,000
The nurses let them in after asking the
patient's name and their relation.

122
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,430
asking the patient's
name and their relation.

123
00:08:59,430 --> 00:09:00,840
- You may enter.
- And no other records?

124
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:01,790
No.

125
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:06,420
Visiting hours are the most
hectic time of the day.

126
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:09,230
Especially earlier, when the
visiting hours started...

127
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:11,800
- Mom!
- Mother, what's wrong?

128
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:14,800
We had a code blue,
so it was more hectic.

129
00:09:16,980 --> 00:09:20,270
And Ms. Yu Ri Hye's ward 2...

130
00:09:20,270 --> 00:09:22,390
While it's in front of the station,

131
00:09:22,390 --> 00:09:25,520
it's not so visible
due to the high table.

132
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:27,130
Even if it's not visible...

133
00:09:27,130 --> 00:09:30,240
How could you not know when
a patient's ventilator was turned off?

134
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,660
Didn't the alarm go off?

135
00:09:31,660 --> 00:09:33,160
I'll explain that.

136
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:35,940
An alarm will sound if there's
a problem with her vitals.

137
00:09:35,940 --> 00:09:38,160
However, she was
breathing on her own.

138
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:39,640
No symptoms would've
been detected.

139
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:41,460
This is why the alarm didn't go off.

140
00:09:41,460 --> 00:09:42,420
Yes.

141
00:09:42,420 --> 00:09:44,000
Chief is correct.

142
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,870
Then how did you discover
that the ventilator was off?

143
00:09:46,870 --> 00:09:48,920
As I told you already,

144
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:50,950
when the visiting hours
ended at 5 p.m.,

145
00:09:50,950 --> 00:09:52,840
and the visitors had left...

146
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:55,440
I went in to replace her
antibiotics, but...

147
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:05,020
Dr. Cha from Anesthesiology
and Pain Medicine

148
00:10:05,020 --> 00:10:07,860
was standing next to the ventilator
which was turned off.

149
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:14,630
You don't have security
cams inside the rooms?

150
00:10:14,630 --> 00:10:15,940
No.

151
00:10:15,940 --> 00:10:19,600
Security cams are not
allowed inside the wards.

152
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:25,050
Go to the security office and check
all the security cam footage.

153
00:10:25,050 --> 00:10:28,030
Get the names of all the doctors and
visitors who were in the ICU.

154
00:10:28,030 --> 00:10:28,710
Yes, sir.

155
00:10:28,710 --> 00:10:30,190
Officer Park, you come with me.

156
00:10:30,190 --> 00:10:31,180
Okay.

157
00:10:33,860 --> 00:10:35,860
You won't even tell me?

158
00:10:35,860 --> 00:10:38,370
I said, the police are here.

159
00:10:38,370 --> 00:10:40,790
There's no way you would've done
that without guardian consent.

160
00:10:40,790 --> 00:10:42,760
If you didn't do it, why can't you say it?
[ Kang Shi Young ]

161
00:10:44,420 --> 00:10:45,920
You know something, huh?

162
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,780
I can leave, right?

163
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:49,410
"A right to remain silent?"

164
00:10:50,390 --> 00:10:52,820
There must be a reason
for your silence.

165
00:10:52,820 --> 00:10:53,630
Fine.

166
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:55,600
Don't say a word until
the truth is revealed.

167
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:56,730
No.

168
00:10:56,730 --> 00:10:58,940
I'll cooperate with
the investigation.

169
00:10:58,940 --> 00:11:00,480
As I did three years ago.

170
00:11:01,860 --> 00:11:03,140
Dr. Cha.

171
00:11:03,140 --> 00:11:04,440
Dr. Cha!

172
00:11:05,530 --> 00:11:06,690
Dr. Cha!

173
00:11:13,770 --> 00:11:14,930
Dr. Cha!

174
00:11:21,290 --> 00:11:22,490
Kang Shi Young.

175
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,260
I promise you.

176
00:11:38,150 --> 00:11:40,750
We meet again, Dr. Cha Yo Han.

177
00:11:49,090 --> 00:11:50,940
You know what?

178
00:11:50,940 --> 00:11:53,800
After I took your case
three years ago,

179
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:56,330
all medical-related
accidents and incidents...

180
00:11:56,330 --> 00:11:58,280
They all come to me.

181
00:11:59,540 --> 00:12:00,700
Have a seat.

182
00:12:02,990 --> 00:12:05,210
I'm practically a doctor,
thanks to you.

183
00:12:05,210 --> 00:12:08,780
When someone at
my station gets sick,

184
00:12:08,780 --> 00:12:10,470
they all come to me first.

185
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:15,710
I guess someone's coming?

186
00:12:15,710 --> 00:12:18,010
Who will conduct the investigation?

187
00:12:18,010 --> 00:12:20,560
Things are becoming more
complicated than we anticipated.

188
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:26,980
Starting now, all interrogation
and examination...

189
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:31,350
will be headed and conducted by
Prosecutor Son Seok Ki.

190
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,890
I ask of you.

191
00:12:48,890 --> 00:12:50,190
Yes, sir.

192
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:04,200
You should've listened to me.

193
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:07,430
I had given you a warning.

194
00:13:09,050 --> 00:13:10,610
You don't remember?

195
00:13:10,610 --> 00:13:12,540
What I want...

196
00:13:12,540 --> 00:13:14,510
is only one thing.

197
00:13:14,510 --> 00:13:18,270
I'm asking you not to do anything.

198
00:13:18,270 --> 00:13:21,110
Please don't...

199
00:13:21,110 --> 00:13:22,450
do anything.

200
00:13:24,670 --> 00:13:26,610
If a doctor doesn't do anything,

201
00:13:26,610 --> 00:13:29,350
then two things
happen to a patient.

202
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:31,610
Either experience death-like pains,

203
00:13:31,610 --> 00:13:34,050
or die after experiencing pain.

204
00:13:34,050 --> 00:13:35,260
I see.

205
00:13:35,260 --> 00:13:39,250
So you did something
today, indeed.

206
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:48,550
That's good. Shall we
get started now?

207
00:13:49,970 --> 00:13:54,010
Today's investigation is regarding the
attempted murder of Yu Ri Hye.

208
00:13:54,010 --> 00:13:56,210
Cha Yo Han has the
right to remain silent.

209
00:13:56,210 --> 00:13:58,190
If you forfeit that right
and make a statement,

210
00:13:58,190 --> 00:14:00,450
it could be used as
evidence against you.

211
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:02,060
Well...

212
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:05,580
Do you have anything
to say before we start?

213
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:08,340
No, I don't.

214
00:14:08,340 --> 00:14:10,400
Well, I do. I'm curious
about something.

215
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:13,890
From about noon today to the
estimated time of the incident,

216
00:14:13,890 --> 00:14:16,460
you were absent for
about four hours.

217
00:14:16,460 --> 00:14:17,840
I had called in sick.

218
00:14:18,810 --> 00:14:20,560
Are you not feeling well?

219
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:22,410
I don't want to answer that.

220
00:14:22,410 --> 00:14:24,810
You're not well. That's too bad.

221
00:14:24,810 --> 00:14:27,050
It's nothing to worry about.

222
00:14:27,050 --> 00:14:28,350
What a shame.

223
00:14:31,610 --> 00:14:33,050
Regardless.

224
00:14:33,050 --> 00:14:36,830
You were absent right up
till the time of the incident.

225
00:14:36,830 --> 00:14:38,300
Is this what you're saying?

226
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:40,080
Yes, it is.

227
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:42,020
Three years ago.

228
00:14:42,020 --> 00:14:44,230
I recall that day.

229
00:14:44,230 --> 00:14:47,980
The first time I sat
with you face-to-face.

230
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:49,430
I mean...

231
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:52,540
If one thing has changed
since then, this time...

232
00:14:52,540 --> 00:14:55,410
your team members will also

233
00:14:55,410 --> 00:14:58,270
be investigated as
reference witnesses.

234
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:00,630
Yes.

235
00:15:00,630 --> 00:15:04,180
Contagion is such a scary thing.

236
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:10,490
Kang Shi Young.

237
00:15:10,490 --> 00:15:12,810
If something happens to me,

238
00:15:12,810 --> 00:15:15,130
you'll be the first to know.

239
00:15:15,130 --> 00:15:17,890
You'll be the first person I tell.

240
00:15:19,070 --> 00:15:20,370
I promise.

241
00:15:22,280 --> 00:15:24,420
Don't worry, Dr. Cha.

242
00:15:24,420 --> 00:15:26,550
I have faith in you.

243
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,850
What will you do?

244
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:38,470
"Do you think Dr. Cha turned off
the ventilator or not?"

245
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:41,110
If the police ask,

246
00:15:41,110 --> 00:15:43,360
how will you answer?

247
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:49,220
Also, do we need to mention

248
00:15:49,220 --> 00:15:52,250
that we were going to
grant Yu Ri Hye's wish?

249
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:53,550
What about it?

250
00:15:53,550 --> 00:15:55,400
Since we told her we
were going to do that,

251
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:57,570
the patient felt hopeful
about seeing her son.

252
00:15:57,570 --> 00:15:59,340
But when that didn't go well,

253
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:02,140
she jumped off.

254
00:16:04,410 --> 00:16:07,650
That is irrelevant to
shutting off the a ventilator.

255
00:16:07,650 --> 00:16:10,270
It's not like one of us turned it off.

256
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:16,650
We're monitoring her.

257
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:19,100
Her vitals are stable for now.

258
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:22,480
We don't know when
she'll be conscious, correct?

259
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:25,170
No. We'll have to see.

260
00:16:41,630 --> 00:16:43,300
[ Hansae Wish Club ]

261
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:50,440
[ Hansae Wish Club ]

262
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:54,380
Hello.

263
00:16:58,740 --> 00:17:00,900
Around 5 p.m. today.

264
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:03,910
About the estimated time
right after the incident.

265
00:17:03,910 --> 00:17:05,430
You were at the scene, correct?

266
00:17:05,430 --> 00:17:07,530
- Yu Ri Hye's ICU ward.
- Yes.

267
00:17:07,530 --> 00:17:08,870
Why did you go there?

268
00:17:08,870 --> 00:17:10,960
I went to see the patient.

269
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:13,930
I heard she tried to kill
herself. I was worried.

270
00:17:13,930 --> 00:17:16,850
Just exactly when and from
whom did you hear this report?

271
00:17:16,850 --> 00:17:20,530
I reported it to Dr. Cha
around 4:45 p.m.

272
00:17:20,530 --> 00:17:22,500
I have the call history.

273
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:24,200
[ Dr. Cha Yo Han, 4:45 p.m. ]

274
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,400
You were notified around 4:45 p.m.,

275
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:28,740
and arrived at the hospital
at about 4:50 p.m.

276
00:17:28,740 --> 00:17:31,230
- Is this correct?
- Yes.

277
00:17:31,230 --> 00:17:33,580
Did you go to the ICU right away?

278
00:17:34,570 --> 00:17:35,690
No, I didn't.

279
00:17:36,730 --> 00:17:37,800
Well then?

280
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:41,780
As I was arriving,

281
00:17:41,780 --> 00:17:44,380
I saw the scene of the suicide jump.

282
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:55,270
I went to the rooftop right away.

283
00:17:55,270 --> 00:17:56,750
The rooftop?

284
00:17:57,770 --> 00:17:59,760
You were worried about the patient.

285
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:03,700
Why go to the rooftop
first and not the ICU?

286
00:18:05,610 --> 00:18:06,880
Is he a fool?

287
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,370
Me?

288
00:18:09,370 --> 00:18:10,900
I meant Dr. Cha.

289
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:13,810
Who'd fall under the most
suspicion regarding this?

290
00:18:13,810 --> 00:18:17,110
Even if he wasn't at the scene,

291
00:18:17,110 --> 00:18:20,160
Dr. Cha has a euthanasia rep sheet.

292
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:22,460
He knows he'll be suspected,

293
00:18:22,460 --> 00:18:24,810
yet he unplugs the
ventilator and denies it?

294
00:18:24,810 --> 00:18:26,870
Do you think Dr. Cha is an idiot?

295
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:30,010
I don't think Dr. Cha is the one

296
00:18:30,010 --> 00:18:31,670
who turned off the ventilator.

297
00:18:31,670 --> 00:18:33,140
No, it's not.

298
00:18:33,140 --> 00:18:34,280
Well then?

299
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:36,790
Is there anyone you suspect?

300
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,700
No, I don't, but...

301
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,300
[ Hansae Wish Club ]

302
00:18:42,370 --> 00:18:44,310
Answer me.

303
00:18:44,310 --> 00:18:47,760
Why did you go to the rooftop,
and what did you do there?

304
00:19:01,380 --> 00:19:03,550
I looked up at the sky.

305
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:30,550
And then...

306
00:19:31,630 --> 00:19:33,050
I looked at the ground.

307
00:19:34,330 --> 00:19:36,750
You looked up to the sky
and then the ground?

308
00:19:40,410 --> 00:19:42,180
And what was there?

309
00:19:42,180 --> 00:19:44,260
The patient, I suppose.

310
00:19:44,260 --> 00:19:46,290
Right before she jumped.

311
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:49,550
What you're saying is,
you stood in that spot

312
00:19:49,550 --> 00:19:53,480
and empathized with her, correct?

313
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:55,360
After that,

314
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:57,990
you must've wanted to do

315
00:19:57,990 --> 00:20:00,160
what the patient desired.

316
00:20:02,450 --> 00:20:04,840
What did the patient want?

317
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:07,740
You said you were to
grant her a wish.

318
00:20:07,740 --> 00:20:09,740
Her son.

319
00:20:09,740 --> 00:20:11,970
She wanted to see her son.

320
00:20:11,970 --> 00:20:13,810
When she couldn't see her son,

321
00:20:13,810 --> 00:20:16,300
she decided to jump to her death.

322
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:20,140
And her next wish is for
you to help her die?

323
00:20:21,630 --> 00:20:23,480
"How she must've desired death.

324
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:25,240
Enough to jump from
such a high place."

325
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:28,900
After you fully empathized with her,

326
00:20:28,900 --> 00:20:31,980
did you go to the ICU
where the patient was?

327
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:34,770
Yes, I did go to the ICU
from the rooftop.

328
00:20:34,770 --> 00:20:37,370
- And the time?
- Five minutes...

329
00:20:37,370 --> 00:20:38,580
after 5 o'clock.

330
00:20:38,580 --> 00:20:41,100
The exact moment the
ventilator was found unplugged.

331
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:44,810
It's also the moment
someone attempted murder.

332
00:20:50,740 --> 00:20:52,430
Today, for the first time,

333
00:20:52,430 --> 00:20:54,600
I really felt that Dr. Cha...

334
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,710
is such an amazing man.

335
00:20:56,710 --> 00:20:59,360
When we performed intubation
on the patient after she jumped,

336
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:01,910
I worried about doing
so and wondered...

337
00:21:04,030 --> 00:21:05,570
if we should be doing it.

338
00:21:05,570 --> 00:21:06,540
And?

339
00:21:06,540 --> 00:21:08,290
But Dr. Cha...

340
00:21:08,290 --> 00:21:10,950
endured everything three years ago,

341
00:21:10,950 --> 00:21:12,880
and put the patient to rest.

342
00:21:15,050 --> 00:21:17,440
This does not mean that Dr. Cha

343
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:19,830
is the one who turned
off the ventilator. No way.

344
00:21:21,270 --> 00:21:24,510
The ventilator was already
off when you arrived?

345
00:21:24,510 --> 00:21:26,030
Yes.

346
00:21:26,030 --> 00:21:28,650
At the exact time and place
where the incident occurred.

347
00:21:28,650 --> 00:21:32,230
It was a coincidence you
arrived right then?

348
00:21:32,230 --> 00:21:33,410
Yes.

349
00:21:34,570 --> 00:21:37,640
Sure, let's say it's the truth.

350
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,340
I'll ask you one more question.

351
00:21:39,340 --> 00:21:41,330
This will be my final reply today.

352
00:21:43,020 --> 00:21:44,550
Says who?

353
00:21:45,830 --> 00:21:47,410
I'm a little tired.

354
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:50,820
This isn't a formal
interrogation, correct?

355
00:21:50,820 --> 00:21:52,330
Should we make it official then?

356
00:21:52,330 --> 00:21:53,480
Be my guest.

357
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:55,870
After you bring an official warrant.

358
00:22:03,750 --> 00:22:05,060
Fine.

359
00:22:05,060 --> 00:22:07,140
This will be your final reply today.

360
00:22:07,140 --> 00:22:09,760
Not because you're tired,

361
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:12,470
but there is one thing left...

362
00:22:12,470 --> 00:22:15,330
I'd really like to know.

363
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,000
It's murder.

364
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:21,140
Pardon?

365
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:25,120
My father is lying in our hospital.

366
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:27,630
Hooked up to a ventilator.

367
00:22:27,630 --> 00:22:30,160
But if some doctor

368
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:33,440
turns off the ventilator without
my or my family's consent,

369
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:35,510
then it's a clear cut murder.

370
00:22:36,610 --> 00:22:39,150
Yu Ri Hye didn't have
her guardian's consent.

371
00:22:39,150 --> 00:22:41,550
We had plenty of time
to gain consent.

372
00:22:42,870 --> 00:22:46,880
I don't think Dr. Cha had any reason
to shut off the ventilator...

373
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:48,590
unbeknownst to the guardian.

374
00:22:54,340 --> 00:22:56,080
Her days were numbered,

375
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:58,370
and she was facing tremendous pain.

376
00:22:58,370 --> 00:23:00,180
She was hooked up to a ventilator

377
00:23:00,180 --> 00:23:02,650
even though she refused
to prolong her life.

378
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:06,170
When you arrived at the ICU,

379
00:23:06,170 --> 00:23:09,050
what if the ventilator
wasn't shut off...

380
00:23:10,140 --> 00:23:12,010
Dr. Cha...

381
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:15,610
What would you have done?

382
00:23:17,610 --> 00:23:19,940
What did you just say?

383
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:22,330
That I was the starting point...

384
00:23:24,890 --> 00:23:26,080
of all this.

385
00:23:27,460 --> 00:23:28,930
What do you mean by that?

386
00:23:30,320 --> 00:23:31,740
Actually...

387
00:23:37,740 --> 00:23:38,920
Yes.

388
00:23:38,920 --> 00:23:40,380
It's been confirmed?

389
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:43,810
Okay.

390
00:23:46,980 --> 00:23:49,240
You should see for yourself.

391
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:52,110
This truth you can't speak of...

392
00:23:52,110 --> 00:23:54,790
To see if it's on security cam
footage or not.

393
00:24:09,810 --> 00:24:11,760
They finished checking
the security cams.

394
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:14,690
I'll listen to your story
after I check the footage.

395
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:33,500
Won Hee, are you okay?

396
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:36,100
What did you tell them?

397
00:24:38,070 --> 00:24:39,450
I'm sorry.

398
00:24:40,530 --> 00:24:42,880
Sorry about what?

399
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:46,110
This all started because of me.

400
00:24:46,110 --> 00:24:48,930
Man, that's not true.

401
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:52,410
Excuse me, can I help you?

402
00:24:52,410 --> 00:24:54,060
We're not seeing any
patients today.

403
00:24:54,060 --> 00:24:56,770
I came to see you doctors.

404
00:25:02,650 --> 00:25:05,760
My younger sister Ri Hye...

405
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:07,830
She's a scaredy-cat.

406
00:25:08,830 --> 00:25:11,710
And for her to jump like that...

407
00:25:12,660 --> 00:25:14,930
She had really wanted to go.

408
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:19,330
I wonder if clinging on
is the right thing.

409
00:25:25,070 --> 00:25:26,920
I know my sister...

410
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:33,850
had composed an advance directive.

411
00:25:33,850 --> 00:25:38,110
If my sister worsens
at this point, then...

412
00:25:39,420 --> 00:25:42,080
I would like to just...

413
00:25:43,770 --> 00:25:46,280
let her go in peace.

414
00:25:50,060 --> 00:25:51,370
I understand.

415
00:25:53,610 --> 00:25:55,970
We'll make sure the
patient doesn't suffer.

416
00:26:00,850 --> 00:26:01,910
Her son...

417
00:26:03,090 --> 00:26:05,140
really won't be coming after all?

418
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:09,230
Her one and only son.

419
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:13,740
Who knew it'd be so difficult
for her to hold his hand?

420
00:26:13,740 --> 00:26:17,090
She couldn't even hold him...

421
00:26:17,090 --> 00:26:19,890
for one last time...

422
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:36,350
After her fall, she's being
transported to the ICU.

423
00:26:36,350 --> 00:26:39,520
After that, this is 5 p.m.,
the speculated time of the incident.

424
00:26:39,520 --> 00:26:42,320
That's Cha Yo Han
heading to the ICU.

425
00:26:45,490 --> 00:26:47,880
- After that...
- Wait.

426
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:49,590
Please rewind.

427
00:26:56,420 --> 00:26:57,730
Why...

428
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:00,700
is he running?

429
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:01,660
Pardon?

430
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:04,460
He's on his way to unplug a patient's
ventilator. Why would he run?

431
00:27:04,460 --> 00:27:05,380
As if...

432
00:27:06,330 --> 00:27:09,090
